 <TITLE>Locking Principles</TITLE> 
</HEAD>

<BODY     >

 <H1>Locking Principles</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<H2>Independence of locks.  It must be possible to lock a resource without re-reading the resource.
</H2>
<BR></UL><UL>
<H2>Multi-resource locking. It must be possible to take out a lock on multiple resources in the same action, and this locking operation must be atomic across these resources.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<H2>Partial resource locking.  It must be possible to take out a lock on a subsection of a resource.</H2>
</UL></P>
